text: Michelle Koh (born 30 September 1990) is a Malaysian professional golfer who qualified for the 2016 Summer Olympics in Rio de Janeiro, Brazil. In college, Koh competed for Campbell University. Koh was part of the women's team in the 2009 Southeast Asian Games that won a bronze medal.
